A letter and declaration of the nobility and gentry of the county of York, to His Excellency the Lord Generall Monck.
1 sheet ([1] p.)
Printed at York, and re-printed at London for John Starkey, [London] : 1659. [i.e. 1660]
Desiring the recall of the secluded members and the establishment of a Free Parliament. The declaration is signed: Tho. Lord Fairfax [and 47 others]. Annotation on Thomason copy: "Feb: 16." Reproduction of the original in the British Library.
